	<div type="textpart" subtype="sub_volume">
	<head>
	<title>LIBER SEXTUS</title>
	</head>
		<div type="textpart" subtype="section">
		<head>
		<title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta">
		PUBLI RUTILII RUFI FRAGMENTA
		</ref></title>
		</head>
			<div type="textpart" subtype="work">
			<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.historiai">
			ΙΣΤΟΡΙΑΙ
			</ref></title></ab>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="1">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.historiai:1">
					<bibl> Macrob. Sat. I, 16:</bibl>
					<quote>
					Rutilus scribit Romanos instituisse nundinas, ut octo quidem dicbus in agris rustici opus facerent, non autem die, intermisso rure, ad mercatum legesque accipiendas Romam venirent, et ut scita atque consulta frequentiore populo referrentur, quoe trinundino die proposita a singulis atque universis facile noscebantur.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation"></note>
					<note type="commentary">Ceterum num haec ex historia petita sint an alio ex opere, haud liquet.</note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
			</div>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="2">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.historiai:2">
					<bibl> Gellius N. A. VII, 14, 10:</bibl>
					<quote>
					Admirationi fuisse aiunt Rutilius et Polybius philosophorum trium cujusque generis facundiam. Violenta, inquiunt, et rapida Carneades dicebat, scita et teretia Critolaus, modesta Diogenes et sobria.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation"></note>
					<note type="commentary">Cf. Macrob. I, 5; Plinius H. N. VII, 30; Lact. XV, 17.</note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
			</div>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="3">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.historiai:3">
					<bibl> Livius XXXIX, 52:</bibl>
					<quote>
					Scipionem et Polybius et Rutilius hoc anno (570 anno U.) mortuum scribunt. Ego neque his neque Valerio assentior, etc.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation"></note>
					<note type="commentary"></note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
			</div>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="4">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.historiai:4">
					<bibl> Plutarch. Marius c. 28:</bibl>
					<quote>
					Ὡς δὲ Ῥουτίλιος ἱστορεῖ, τὰ μὲν ἄλλα φιλαλήθης ἀνὴρ καὶ χρηστὸς, ἰδίᾳ δὲ τῷ Μαρίῳ προσκεκρουκὼς, καὶ τῆς ἕκτης ἔτυχεν ὑπατείας, ἀργύριον εἰς τὰς φυλὰς καταβαλὼν πολὺ, καὶ πριάμενος τὸν Μέτελλον ἐκκροῦσαι τῆς ἀρχῆς, Οὐαλέριον δὲ Φλάκκον ὑπηρέτην μᾶλλον ἢ συνάρχοντα τῆς ὑπατείας λαβεῖν.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation">Rutilius, bonus alioqui vir et verax, sed cui privatim cum Mario offensae intercesserint, auctor est divisa tributim pecunia Marium sextum consulatum obtinuisse: simulque id, ut Metello repulso Valerius Flaccus sibi administer magis quam collega daretur. </note>
					<note type="commentary"></note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
			</div>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="5">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.historiai:5">
					<bibl> Idem Pempei. c. 37:</bibl>
					<quote>
					Πομπήιον, οὗ τὸν πατέρα παμπόνηρον ἀπέδειξεν ὁ Ῥουτίλιος ἐν ταῖς Ἱστορίαις.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation"> Pompeii patrem Rutilius in Historiis pessimum fuisse hominem demonstravit. </note>
					<note type="commentary">Quare Theophanes (fr. 1) in bistoria sua calumniis Rutilium persecutus esse videtur. Lege antecedentia ap. Plutarch. Locus a Krausio omissus.</note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
			</div>
			<div type="textpart" >
			<cit n="6">
				<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.historiai:6">
					<bibl> Athenaeus XII, p. 543, A:</bibl>
					<quote>
					Διαβόητος δ ̓ ἦν παρὰ Ῥωμαίοις καὶ Σίττιος ἐπὶ τρυφῇ καὶ μαλακίᾳ, ὥς φησι Ῥουτίλιος.
					</quote>
					<note type="translation"> Sittius quoque ob luxuriam et molliticm apud Romanos famosus erat, ut Rutilius dicit. </note>
					<note type="commentary"></note>
				</ref>
			</cit>
			</div>
			</div>
			<div type="textpart" subtype="work">
			<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua">
			DE VITA SUA
			</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" subtype="book">
				<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libro_i">
				E LIBRO I
				</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="7">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libro_i:7">
						<bibl> Charisius II, p. 176 ed. Putsch.:</bibl>
						<quote>
						P. Rutilius Rufus De vita sua libro primo: Pompeius elaboravit, uti populum Romanum nosset, eumque artificiose salutaret.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"></note>
						<note type="commentary"></note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				</div>
				<div type="textpart" subtype="book">
				<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libro_ii">
				E LIBRO II
				</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="8">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libro_ii:8">
						<bibl> Idem I, p. 100:</bibl>
						<quote>
						P. Rutilius de vita sua Ubro secundo: Animo, inquit, constante.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"></note>
						<note type="commentary"></note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				</div>
				<div type="textpart" subtype="book">
				<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libro_iii">
				E LIBRO III
				</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="9">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libro_iii:9">
						<bibl> Idem I, 105:</bibl>
						<quote>
						Familiare recte P. Rutilius De vita sua libro tertio: Pro L. familiare veniebam.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"></note>
						<note type="commentary"></note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				</div>
				<div type="textpart" subtype="book">
				<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libro_iv">
				E LIBRO IV
				</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="10">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libro_iv:10">
						<bibl> Idem I, p. 119:</bibl>
						<quote>
						P. quoque Rutilius De vita sua libro quarto, Scaurus libro tertio: Vectigalium se minus fructos.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"></note>
						<note type="commentary"></note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				</div>
				<div type="textpart" subtype="book">
				<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libro_v">
				E LIBRO V
				</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="11">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libro_v:11">
						<bibl> Idem I, p. 112:</bibl>
						<quote>
						P. Rutilius De vita sua V. Ex orbi terrarum.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"></note>
						<note type="commentary"></note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="12">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libro_v:12">
						<bibl> Idem p. 96:</bibl>
						<quote>
						Aedile, ab hoc oedile, non oedili. P. Rutilius De vita sua quinto.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"></note>
						<note type="commentary"></note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				</div>
				<div type="textpart" subtype="book">
				<ab><title><ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libris_incertis">
				E LIBRIS INCERTIS
				</ref></title></ab>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="13">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libris_incertis:13">
						<bibl> Diomedes I, p. 371 ed. Pulsch.:</bibl>
						<quote>
						Sino, sini, ut P. Rutilius De vita sua: Quodsi me invitum abire sinisset.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"></note>
						<note type="commentary"></note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="14">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libris_incertis:14">
						<bibl> Idem p. 372:</bibl>
						<quote>
						P. Rutilius De vita sua: Uni una ostentura est.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"></note>
						<note type="commentary"></note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				<div type="textpart" >
				<cit n="15">
					<ref target="http://www.dfhg-project.org/DFHG/index.php?volume=Volumen tertium#urn:lofts:fhg.3.publius_rutilius_rufus.publi_rutilii_rufi_fragmenta.de_vita_sua.e_libris_incertis:15">
						<bibl> Isidorus Hispal. Origg. XX, 11:</bibl>
						<quote>
						Lecticoe sive plutei lecti, de quibus Rutilius (vg. Satilius) Rufus De vita sua: Primum, inquit, contra consuetudinem imperatorum ipse pro lectiw lecticis utebatur.
						</quote>
						<note type="translation"></note>
						<note type="commentary"></note>
					</ref>
				</cit>
				</div>
				</div>
			</div>
